      <abstract>
        <p>The authors report a case of esophageal hematoma in a 35-year-old man after esophageal variceal sclerotherapy with intravariceal injection of 5% ethanolamine oleate. A huge submucosal hematoma of the esophageal wall was demonstrated endoscopically and radiologically. Resolution occurred spontaneously after conservative treatment.</p>
      </abstract>
